~ start
It looks like a spellbook, but after taking a closer look it's actually a journal of sorts.
...Should I read it?
- Sure.
	I flip it open to the first page.
	"Day I - I have no idea where I am. The floor breaks away to show an ominous purple void, and the environment here don't just appear different from home, it looks like an entirely different plane of existence."
	"I've come to a few conclusions, and soon I will use these hypotheses to formulate a way to get back home. The first and weakest hypothesis is that this is a dream, unlikely since I've been here for a few days already."
	"Hypothesis two is I've been trapped in an illusion by some spectral entity looking to get revenge on the Clan for our past actions. This feels the most plausible."
	"Hypothesis three is I've been transported to a pocket dimension. There are old stories of dedicated mages able to do something like that, but no one knows if they're real. Not sure what to do in that situation."
	"I'll keep this journal as a means of documenting my progress, or at the very least someone will be able to find this if I can't get back. if you find this book randomly laying around, assume the worst as you read on."
	- Keep going => part2
	- Stop reading => finish
- Nah. => finish

~ part2
There's a bunch of pages just describing them running around the wastes trying to survive. I flip to a page that looks more interesting...
"Day XII - I've found a village of non-hostile individuals. The strangest thing about most of them is that they have no fur and instead have very rough and coarse skin on their entire body."
"I did meet someone more similar in build to myself, though. A feline mage known simply as 'The Mage'. They were somewhat abrasive, but said they enjoyed meeting someone who shared similarities to them."
"The species of furless individuals are supposedly called 'Humans'. The Mage was surprised to hear that humans don't exist where I come from, and never have. They said something interesting when I mentioned where I came from, though."
"They claimed that such a place doesn't exist. In a somewhat mocking tone, they told me that I'll figure it out eventually. I changed the subject and eventually went on my way."
- Keep going => part3
- Stop reading => END

~ part3
I skip ahead by another few pages since it just describes her moving in.
"Day XV - More training with The Fighter. My performance was terrible, I couldn't stop thinking about what The Mage was saying to me the past few days. But before I could voice my frustrations, a new threat emerged."
"A shambling zombie in red armor wandered into the village, muttering about vile magic and attacking the villagers, shouting about freeing them from some kind of spell. They didn't last long when Fighter and I teamed up."
"With no better place to put it, we tied it up and left it in the storeroom for now. It kept shouting about evil magic, and The Fighter seemed upset by something. They left before I got the chance to ask."
- Keep going => part4
- Stop reading => finish

~ part4
do MusicController.music_stop()
[speed=0.5]"Day XVII - I feel like I'm going to throw up."
[speed=0.5]"I finally decided to go to see the 'File Dumps' for myself. I thought at best it could give me a way to get home, at worst it would give us a clue as to why the zombie appeared from that direction."
[speed=0.5]"I shouldn't have gone. I shouldn't have gone. I shouldnthavegone.ishouldnthavegoneishouldnthavegoneishouldnthavegone[shake rate=20 level=10]ishouldnthavegoneishouldnthavegoneishouldnthavegone[/shake][shake rate=20 level=20]ishouldnthavegoneishouldnthavegone[/shake][shake rate=20 level=30]Ishouldn'thavegone[/shake]"
