- Keep going
	do MusicController.play_memory_music()
	[speed=0.5]"Day XXIV - I can still feel knots in my chest. During my panic, Fighter was apparently convinced by Mage and Healer to ignore me. One of the few people I thought I could trust."
	[speed=0.5]"But no, it was the zombie who comforted me. Of all the people to step forward and help me at my most vulnerable, it was the zombie. After everything I did to him."
	[speed=0.5]"He called himself The Vagabond, and apparently while I was hiding myself away he came to his senses and befriended the villagers. He's not even particularly violent or aggressive."
	[speed=0.5]"He offered to explain everything. We went back to the File Dumps where he asked me to find what made me so upset. I still felt the knot in my chest when I picked it up."
	[speed=0.5]"I felt it all coming back. I just wanted to throw it as far as I could and forget everything so I could pretend like I was just another survivor in this wasteland. But he stopped me."
	[speed=0.5]"And then he asked me to tell him about her."
	[speed=0.5]"I suppose I didn't remember everything about my life when I arrived here. I had forgotten that real friends were those who would sacrifice their well-being for each other. So I suppose my closest friend is the zombie, now."
	[speed=0.5]"I haven't given up hope that I'll get out of the wastes someday, but my perspective has changed. There's no need to actively attempt to escape anymore, especially not when there are people willing to create communities."
	[speed=0.5]"It'll be strange, though. Rather than returning to a place I already knew, I'll be going there for the first time. Like changing your residence." 
	[speed=0.5]"Will this knowledge stay with me when I arrive? Are we always actors, always aware that our lives are predetermined?"
	[speed=0.5]"Or maybe it's just the stories that are predetermined. Maybe we all live our lives as normal until we're given a narrative to act out. Maybe what The Creator crafts is just one day in our lives. I like that thought."
	[speed=0.5]"I probably won't write in this again anytime soon. So if you do find this laying around in the middle of nowhere, don't assume I'm dead."
	...The rest of the pages are blank. There's a photo tucked in-between the last entry and the blank pages afterwards, though.
	There's two young fox girls, standing side by side in school uniforms. Button up shirts, skirts, matching backpacks, and apparently their school's dress code required them to tie their hair...fur, back behind their head.
	One of the girls is unmistakably Zulie. She has a scowl as she looks down at her outfit. She looks like she wants to rip it to shreds.
	I don't know who the other girl is. She has a slightly lighter fur color and white around her muzzle, unlike Zulie's pure orange. They're smiling, they think Zulie's reaction to the uniform is funny. Or at least amusing.
	I turn the photo over and see something written on the back.
	[speed=0.2]"Kira & Zulie's first day of 1st grade."
